Some, however, thought that if the marriage was contracted in accordance with the lex Aelia sentia, the offspring is a Latin by birth, because in this hypothesis the lex Aelia Sentia and J uma Norbana confer a capacity of civil marriage, and a civil marriage always transmits to the offspring the status of the father: if the marriage was otherwise contracted, they held the offspring acquires by Gentile law the status of his mother. However, it is now certain that the offspring is a Roman citizen in either case, · for the senatusconsult
